Mauritius and other countries for the first time found Omicron virus infection cases-Xinhua Xinhua Agency, Beijing, December 12 Xinhua News Agency reporters abroad:Mauritius, Cyprus and Malawi recently reported the first cases of infection with the new crown variant virus Omicron strain. Mauritius reported the first two cases of Omicron strain infection in the country on the 10th. According to the health minister of the country, Kelesh Jagutpal, one infected person arrived in Mauritius on November 27 from South Africa;Another infected person for Mauritius local residents, He and a recent trip to South Africa after returning to contact, In November 30 nucleic acid test positive.After hospital isolation treatment, The two infected nucleic acid test results are negative, Now have returned to their place of residence. The Ministry of Health of Cyprus announced on the 10th that the country has confirmed three cases of Omicron virus infection for the first time. The three are students, who returned from a trip abroad earlier this month. They were not hospitalized because they were mild. In order to prevent the spread of Omicron virus, the Cypriot government has continuously stepped up prevention and control efforts. From December 6 to January 10 next year, passengers over the age of 12 who arrive by air must receive nucleic acid tests at their own expense at the airport. The Cypriot Ministry of Health also announced on the 10th,Pfizer's new crown vaccine will begin to be administered to children between the ages of 5 and 11 in the country. Malawi's health minister, Kumbizze Chiponda, said Wednesday that the country had found three cases of Omicron infection for the first time. The country's health authorities sequenced the genome of 12 COVID-19 positive samples collected from November 9 to December 2 and found the three cases.
